FT  18 OCT 94 / International Company News: Heinz signs agreement to buy
Kraft frozen meals business
H. J. Heinz, the US food group, said it had signed an agreement to buy The
All American Gourmet Company, the California-based maker of The Budget
Gourmet frozen meals and side dishes, from Kraft General Foods, part of the
Philip Morris tobacco and food group, writes Richard Tomkins in New York.
Mr David Sculley, senior vice-president in charge of Heinz's frozen food and
Weight Watchers businesses, said the acquisition would enable Heinz to
become a low-cost producer in the frozen foods category. Kraft said it was
selling the company as part of a strategic realignment of its food
operations.
